Namibia to Pay War Veterans N$750 Million, Namibian Reports

-- B y   C h a m w e   K a i r a
-- 
2011-11-29T07:39:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/namibia-to-pay-war-veterans-n-750-million-namibian-reports.html
Namibia’s Ministry of Veterans
Affairs will pay a total of 750 million Namibian dollars ($90
million) over three years to 13,000 veterans of the country’s
liberation war, the Namibian reported citing the permanent
secretary in the ministry, William Amagulu.  The soldiers fought on the side of the ruling party Swapo
in the war that resulted in independence from  South Africa  in
1990. There are 45,000 veterans registered with the ministry,
Amagulu said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chamwe Kaira in Windhoek at 
 ckaira@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
